I asked you,

578
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:24,130
left or right?

579
00:37:24,630 --> 00:37:26,900
Left or right?

580
00:37:26,920 --> 00:37:27,610
Does that matter?

581
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:31,010
If it was a left turn,
you're just circling around in Dongping.

582
00:37:32,670 --> 00:37:33,860
If it was a right turn,

583
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,380
then we're in Jiangnan now.

584
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,650
See how familiar he is
with the roads.

585
00:37:43,670 --> 00:37:45,010
That's the charm
of a seasoned investigator.

586
00:37:45,230 --> 00:37:45,780
Respect.

587
00:37:48,510 --> 00:37:48,940
We turned right.

588
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,380
Off-site investigation.

589
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:03,420
Look,

590
00:38:04,440 --> 00:38:06,260
you don't have to feel pressured.

591
00:38:07,150 --> 00:38:08,780
You're just here
to assist with some questions.

592
00:38:09,550 --> 00:38:11,010
I ask, and you answer.

593
00:38:12,150 --> 00:38:14,170
Tell us what you know
and what you're willing to share.

594
00:38:14,190 --> 00:38:14,900
But of course,

595
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,530
you'll need to stand by what you say.

596
00:38:17,710 --> 00:38:18,940
I'll be responsible too.

597
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:21,740
If there's something you don't know
or don't want to say,

598
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:22,820
you don't have to.

599
00:38:23,230 --> 00:38:23,980
I'm not here to force you

600
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:25,610
or pin anything on you.

601
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,260
I know,

602
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:28,900
being in this seat all of a sudden

603
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:29,740
is quite a shock.

604
00:38:30,150 --> 00:38:31,460
I'm only here

605
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:32,610
because of orders from above.

606
00:38:33,480 --> 00:38:33,980
We each

607
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:35,460
have our roles to play.

608
00:38:43,190 --> 00:38:44,130
That Wanchuan Mine,

609
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:47,780
where an accident happened
a few days ago,

610
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:49,090
is in your jurisdiction, right?

611
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:52,170
So was your Criminal Investigation Unit

612
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:53,820
one of the first

613
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:55,300
to arrive on the scene?

614
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:58,300
What about it?

615
00:38:59,110 --> 00:39:00,380
There was a mine accident,

616
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:01,690
casualties,

617
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:03,780
maybe a confrontation.

618
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:05,010
We've gotta be there,

619
00:39:05,030 --> 00:39:05,940
control the scene,

620
00:39:06,110 --> 00:39:06,980
and manage the situation.

621
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,010
So I asked you,

622
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:10,050
was your unit

623
00:39:10,110 --> 00:39:12,300
one of the first to arrive on the scene?

624
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,860
So when the police dispatch center

625
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:19,460
got the report about the accident,

626
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:20,900
they didn't call

627
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,740
the local police station
or the law and order brigade first

628
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,570
but called Criminal Investigation Unit.

629
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:25,610
Is that right?

630
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,490
So when you got to the scene,

631
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:31,340
you must've been standing
right up front.

632
00:39:36,510 --> 00:39:37,130
In the middle?

633
00:39:38,590 --> 00:39:39,340
The very back?

634
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,740
If you were in the back,

635
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,860
that gave you a chance to slip away

636
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:44,740
without getting noticed.

637
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,130
Was there any moment

638
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:48,340
you moved around the site on your own?

639
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,210
No.

640
00:39:58,760 --> 00:39:59,130
See,

641
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:01,780
you must not have heard it clearly.

642
00:40:02,230 --> 00:40:03,170
What I asked you is,

643
00:40:03,710 --> 00:40:04,860
did you act alone at any point

644
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:07,260
that night at the accident site?

645
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:08,860
Hong Liang, can you not
understand human language?

646
00:40:09,190 --> 00:40:09,900
I told you

647
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:12,940
I didn't act alone. I didn't!

648
00:40:17,190 --> 00:40:18,210
Why are you pinning this on me,
Hong Liang?

649
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:18,900
No...

650
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:19,530
- Don't move.
- Hong Liang.

651
00:40:19,670 --> 00:40:20,340
Wait, I...

652
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,300
What is wrong with you?

653
00:40:21,480 --> 00:40:22,050
Don't...

654
00:40:22,070 --> 00:40:23,090
Don't buckle it.

655
00:40:23,150 --> 00:40:24,170
I'm telling the truth.

656
00:40:24,190 --> 00:40:25,740
Did I say anything wrong?

657
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,210
I've answered your question!

658
00:40:27,710 --> 00:40:28,530
I just said

659
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,490
we both have to take responsibility
for our words.

660
00:40:35,070 --> 00:40:35,900
I gave you a chance.

661
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,690
But you didn't cherish it.

662
00:40:44,590 --> 00:40:45,860
Take a look at this video.

663
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:50,490
I recorded it.

664
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,050
I only sent it to Chao.

665
00:40:55,670 --> 00:40:56,380
Wan Chao, right?

666
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:59,010
He sent it to us.

667
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:00,690
You saw that guy in the video
that night.

668
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:01,940
What else did he do later?

669
00:41:04,190 --> 00:41:04,690
That day,

670
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:07,300
I shot this video from this spot.

671
00:41:07,550 --> 00:41:08,650
After the man left,

672
00:41:09,070 --> 00:41:09,690
I came in.

673
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,300
The floor was covered in oil.

674
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:13,780
Way more than you see here now.

675
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:15,860
The official police conclusion was

676
00:41:16,550 --> 00:41:18,820
that the oil pipe was old

677
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:20,010
and leaking.

678
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:23,340
But a leak should be slow,
dripping little by little.

679
00:41:23,630 --> 00:41:25,980
How could it cause such a huge puddle?

680
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:29,740
Someone clearly opened the valve

681
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,300
and let the oil

682
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:32,740
gush out all at once.

683
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:35,980
Look here.

684
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:39,010
This is obviously from a spray.

685
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,380
Would a drip splash this far?

686
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:42,610
Leave marks like this?

687
00:41:43,110 --> 00:41:43,610
Also,

688
00:41:44,150 --> 00:41:45,490
after the oil drained,

689
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,130
the winch lost traction.

690
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:49,610
That lifting cage

691
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,090
would fall off for sure.

692
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:52,690
That's no work accident.

693
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,690
It's obviously man-made sabotage.

694
00:41:55,630 --> 00:41:57,130
You saw that video too.

695
00:41:57,480 --> 00:41:57,980
This man

696
00:41:58,550 --> 00:42:00,530
turned clockwise, back toward me.

697
00:42:00,710 --> 00:42:02,460
He must've reattached

698
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,490
the valve

699
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:06,610
to fake a leak afterward.

700
00:42:07,070 --> 00:42:08,340
Doesn't that make sense?

701
00:42:13,670 --> 00:42:14,260
Manager,

702
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:15,940
was there anyone suspicious

703
00:42:16,030 --> 00:42:17,340
who entered the winch room

704
00:42:17,710 --> 00:42:18,980
before the accident?

705
00:42:19,670 --> 00:42:20,860
I'm not sure.

706
00:42:21,550 --> 00:42:23,780
I was in the duty room that night,

707
00:42:24,110 --> 00:42:26,940
not handling the personnel arrangements.

708
00:42:28,320 --> 00:42:29,260
Do you have the list

709
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:31,130
of the workers
who went underground that day?

710
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,900
You should ask Chen Hui about this.

711
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:36,130
It was his team that went down
that shift.

712
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:38,690
He works with the miners every day,

713
00:42:38,710 --> 00:42:40,050
eats with them, and sleeps with them.

714
00:42:40,550 --> 00:42:41,130
He knows.

715
00:42:42,150 --> 00:42:42,490
Okay.

716
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:43,530
Thanks for your time.

717
00:42:44,150 --> 00:42:46,380
Please don't talk to anyone about
what we discussed today.

718
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:47,300
This stays confidential.

719
00:42:47,670 --> 00:42:49,860
If anything comes up,
contact us directly.

720
00:42:50,630 --> 00:42:51,460
Give him our number.

721
00:42:52,360 --> 00:42:52,860
Thank you.

722
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:55,380
Jiang Hongjun.

723
00:42:57,150 --> 00:42:57,860
Section chief rank?

724
00:42:58,920 --> 00:43:00,860
Your base salary

725
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:01,900
is just over 5,000 yuan a month.

726
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:03,340
And last month,

727
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:04,260
with all the bonuses and extras,

728
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:06,090
you took home 6,742 yuan.

729
00:43:08,150 --> 00:43:08,860
According to what you said,

730
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:11,570
your kid's in school,
and your wife's unemployed.

731
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:13,530
You don't have any family business

732
00:43:13,800 --> 00:43:14,940
or rental properties.

733
00:43:16,070 --> 00:43:18,260
So your whole family
lives on your paycheck.

734
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,570
Do you have any other income sources?

735
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,380
Finances?

736
00:43:23,110 --> 00:43:24,170
I can stand up to any scrutiny.

737
00:43:24,440 --> 00:43:25,340
No extra income?

738
00:43:25,360 --> 00:43:25,900
None.

739
00:43:26,110 --> 00:43:27,460
Then any extra assets?

740
00:43:27,550 --> 00:43:28,300
None.

741
00:43:28,630 --> 00:43:30,690
No extra income, nor extra assets?

742
00:43:30,710 --> 00:43:31,090
No.

743
00:43:31,230 --> 00:43:31,980
Then where

744
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:34,130
did the 3.23 million in cash

745
00:43:34,150 --> 00:43:36,650
and 28 gold bars come from?

746
00:43:49,510 --> 00:43:50,420
You've got it all wrong.

747
00:43:52,710 --> 00:43:53,570
My brother

748
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:56,050
does business abroad.

749
00:43:56,510 --> 00:43:57,610
It's not safe over there,

750
00:43:57,630 --> 00:43:59,460
so he stores his money in China.

751
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:01,530
All that money is his,

752
00:44:01,550 --> 00:44:02,050
and it's in his house.

753
00:44:02,070 --> 00:44:03,170
When did I ever say

754
00:44:03,190 --> 00:44:04,820
it was found in your brother's house?

755
00:44:27,440 --> 00:44:31,080
♪Had it not been for you♪

756
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:34,840
♪I'd never have known how love feels♪

757
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:40,080
♪The darker the night,
the brighter the stars shine♪

758
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:46,040
♪If not for the words you let me hear♪

759
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:49,800
♪How could I break from chains of fear♪

760
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:55,760
♪To feel myself rise, then gently fall♪

761
00:44:57,560 --> 00:45:01,280
♪No rest, no peace, no dare♪

762
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:09,360
♪No dreams, no thoughts,
no confusion or fear♪

763
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:16,200
♪No fight, no cry, no words to lend♪

764
00:45:16,200 --> 00:45:21,680
♪I owed you nothing in the end♪

765
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:30,840
♪But still, I thank you♪

766
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:34,840
♪For blooming my midnights♪

767
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:37,280
♪Even through roads both rough and wide♪

768
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:42,200
♪You traced the shape of free inside♪

769
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:45,960
♪Someone will always hold that grace♪

770
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:49,680
♪A love that time cannot erase♪

771
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:52,280
♪And what I once clung to
with all my might♪

772
00:45:52,280 --> 00:45:57,680
♪Now softly lands beyond the light♪

773
00:45:57,680 --> 00:46:01,320
♪No sleep, no rest, no will to try♪

774
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:10,880
♪No dreams, no thoughts,
no confusion or fear♪

775
00:46:12,680 --> 00:46:16,280
♪No fight, no cry, no words to lend♪

776
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:22,240
♪But love will bloom in me till the end♪
